article.description: Jordon Varnado scored 23 points and grabbed 13 rebounds, and Kevin Baker sank the winning 3-pointer in overtime to lift Troy to a 73-72 win over Louisiana-Monroe on Monday night.
article.headline: Baker's deep 3 lifts Troy past Louisiana-Monroe 73-72 in OT
article.linkText: Baker's deep 3 lifts Troy past Louisiana-Monroe 73-72 in OT
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Jordon Varnado scored 23 points and grabbed 13 rebounds, and Kevin Baker sank the winning 3-pointer in overtime to lift Troy to a 73-72 win over Louisiana-Monroe on Monday night. Troy, trailing by two in OT after Louisiana-Monroe got a bucket from Travis Munnings to make it 72-70, got the ball to Baker and he launched it from deep behind the arc with 3.4 left. UL-M's final shot, a mid-court attempt from Nick Cappola, fell short. Juan Davis Jr. added 12 points for Troy (14-12, 6-6 Sun Belt) and Baker finished with 11, including three from long range. The Trojans shot 41 percent from the field and edged Louisiana-Monroe 13-6 at the free throw line. Munnings and Marcus Washington scored 18 points apiece for Louisiana Monroe (7-19, 1-12). Sam McDaniel had 15 and Marvin Jean-Pierre 13, including the jumper with 26 seconds left in regulation to tie it at 64-all and force overtime.
